sentences: Bruce Duncan "Utah" Phillips (May 15, 1935 – May 23, 2008) was an American labor organizer, folk singer, storyteller and poet.

Phillips met folk singer Rosalie Sorrels in the early 1950s, and remained a close friend of hers.
